se:Description.se:Title: Geomorphologic Feature Natural Default Style
se:Description.se:Abstract: Proposal for the portrayal style for types of natural geomorphologic features based on color codes: Some rules consider color codes associated to the landform genesis or geomorphologic environments (References 1 and 2). In other cases (Reference 3) the color code is not directly related to any specific geomorphologic environment. Constructional -, destructional -, degradation -, relic -, exhumed -, buried - or erosional features has the same colour as the volcanic, hydrothermal, slopeGravitational, NivalPeriglacialPermafrost, glacial, eolian, marineLittoralCoastalWetland, karstChemicalWeathering, alluvialFluvial, lacustrine or impact NaturalGeomorphologicFeatureTypeValue to which is related (symbol ad-hoc).
